      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "This is a special case of [486]."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "c24272052326938db935f23aed5c6b15eea69cbdb4c661d3cd415a7687339ee3",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $1\\leq n_1<n_2<\\cdots$ be an arbitrary sequence of integers, each with an associated residue class $a_i\\pmod{n_i}$. Let $A$ be the set of integers $n$ such that for every $i$ either $n<n_i$ or $n\\not\\equiv a_i\\pmod{n_i}$. Must the logarithmic density of $A$ exist?"
    }
  },
